==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Straight-joint
<hw>Straight"-joint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>Having straight joints.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Applied to a floor the boards of which are so laid that the joints
form a continued line transverse to the length of the boards
themselves.</def> <au>Brandle & C.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In the United
States, applied to planking or flooring put together without the tongue
and groove, the pieces being laid edge to edge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straight-lined</ent>⟦br⟧
